title: About Me
text:
I aspire to work in the dairy industry with precision technology to improve dairy cow reproduction. To successfully bake sourdough bread



May 2025: BS in Animal Science at University of New Hampshire Aug 2025-current: MS in Agricultural Science at University of New Hampshire



Northwood Veternary Hospital (June 2025 - Aug 2025) - Vet Technician
Stratford Animal Hospital (June 2022 - May 2025) - Vet Technician
Fairchild Dairy Teaching and Research Center (Jan 2023 - May 2025) - Animal Caretaker, Research Worker
Undergraduate Thesis: Precision Dairy Technologies and Dairy Cow Health with Dr. Claira Seely - Thesis Title: Effect of Pulsed Electromagnetic Field Therapy on Milk Quality in Organic Dairy Cows
Cooperative Real Education in Agricultural Management (Aug 2023 - May 2024) - President of course in Spring 2024
